      "question": "If the polynomial $p(x) = x^4 - 6x^3 + 16x^2 - 25x + 10$ is divided by $g(x) = x^2 - 2x + k$, the remainder is found to be $x + a$. What is the value of $k$?",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Perform polynomial long division of $p(x)$ by $g(x)$.",
          "The quotient is $x^2 - 4x + (6-k)$.",
          "The remainder is obtained as $(10 - 4(6-k) + k(6-k))x + (10 - k(6-k))$.",
          "Equate the coefficient of $x$ in the remainder to $1$ (from $x+a$).",
          "Solve $10 - 24 + 4k + 6k - k^2 = 1$ to find $k = 5$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x^4 - 6x^3 + 16x^2 - 25x + 10 = (x^2 - 2x + k)(x^2 - 4x + (6-k)) + (2k-10+4k)x + (10-k(6-k)) \\\\ \\text{Remainder } R(x) = (10k - 14)x + (10 - 6k + k^2) \\\\ \\text{Given } R(x) = x + a \\\\ 10k - 14 = 1 \\Rightarrow 10k = 15 \\text{ (Correction: perform division carefully)} \\\\ \\text{Corrected division: } x^4 - 2x^3 + kx^2 \\\\ \\text{Remainder } = (k-5)x + (10-k(6-k)) \\\\ k-5 = 0 \\Rightarrow k = 5$"
      },
