    {
      "question": "When $f(x) = 2x^3 + ax^2 + bx - 6$ is divided by $(x-1)$ and $(x+2)$, the remainders are $0$ and $12$ respectively. What is the value of $a - b$?",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the Remainder Theorem: $f(1) = 0$ and $f(-2) = 12$.",
          "Substitute $x=1$ into $f(x)$: $2(1)^3 + a(1)^2 + b(1) - 6 = 0 \\Rightarrow a + b = 4$.",
          "Substitute $x=-2$ into $f(x)$: $2(-8) + a(4) + b(-2) - 6 = 12 \\Rightarrow 4a - 2b = 34 \\Rightarrow 2a - b = 17$.",
          "Solve the system of linear equations: $(a+b) + (2a-b) = 4 + 17 \\Rightarrow 3a = 21 \\Rightarrow a = 7$.",
          "Find $b$: $7 + b = 4 \\Rightarrow b = -3$.",
          "Calculate $a - b = 7 - (-3) = 10$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$f(1) = 2 + a + b - 6 = 0 \\Rightarrow a+b = 4 \\\\ f(-2) = -16 + 4a - 2b - 6 = 12 \\Rightarrow 4a - 2b = 34 \\Rightarrow 2a - b = 17 \\\\ (a+b) + (2a-b) = 4 + 17 \\Rightarrow 3a = 21 \\Rightarrow a = 7 \\\\ 7 + b = 4 \\Rightarrow b = -3 \\\\ a - b = 7 - (-3) = 10$"
      },
